        "text": "Incalculable complexity is surfacing increasingly at the social level. For example: culturally, we have moved from English freemen and surfs doing the farming with hand tools, to industrialized mechaniza- tion, then to complete industrialization of farming, now to global agribusiness. As the world becomes more and more interconnected we experience the consequences. There is an explosion of combinations of interactions driving the complexity we are experiencing. The numbers, the density, and the rapidity of com- munication between people, across cultures and con- tinents begin to create patterns similar to those we have discovered in physics, chemistry, and biology. One hundred years ago we understood such over- whelming complexity only in of physics, chem- istry and microbiology.\n"
