      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "517604f03f7ceb76",
        "text": "# THREE COMPLEXITY FILTERS\n1 RELEVANCE\nIn managing human complexity, relevance is first and biggest filter to apply, the first step toward reduc- ing complexity--by focusing only on what is relevant, by omitting or positively excluding the irrelevant the largest set of interactions and distractions are re- moved.\n"
      },
      "date": 1635962378882
    },
    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "282faf6de1d1387e",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "282faf6de1d1387e",
        "text": "2 LOCALNESS\nFrom my point of view, most of the truly human forms of beauty are local and intimate, where we are in contact with—dirt, water, sunlight, paths, visible landscapes, fauna, friends and foes, hand tools, gath- erings, conversations, listening, understanding, mar- ket places, homes, work places. The creation of Aes- thetics (Beauty) needs agoras—places where we have conversations about what we care about, where we make shared commitments and take action to- gether, and where through trial and error we safely learn what we are capable of together.\n"
      },
      "date": 1635962382642
